citation: Proclamation under the Australian Consumer Law (Tasmania) Act 2010 (Tas)
text:
Proclamation under the Australian Consumer Law (Tasmania) Act 2010

I, the Governor in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, acting with the advice of the Executive Council, by this my proclamation made under section 2 of the Australian Consumer Law (Tasmania) Act 2010 fix 1 January 2011 as the day on which the provisions of that Act, apart from sections 1 and 2 and Parts 6 and 7 , commence.

17 December 2010

PETER G. UNDERWOOD

Governor

By His Excellency's Command,

NICK McKIM

Minister for Corrections and Consumer Protection

Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 29 December 2010

This proclamation is administered in the Department of Justice.
